args:
When Elisanne and Julietta arrive in the jungle,
they find it full of numerous tricky traps.
But when Siren's singing puts them in true
danger, the prince rushes in to save them.
Elisanne and Julietta go deep into\nthe jungle in search of treasure...
Is something the matter, Julietta?\nYou are terribly quiet.
(Aaaah! I'm finally alone with her!\nSo what do I do NOW?!)
(I should talk to her! ...Except I am so\nnervous, I can't formulate words.)
Ah, I see the problem now.
You are merely keeping a close watch on\nyour surroundings. An excellent idea in\na jungle as dense as this one.
Yes, by keeping your focus keen, you will\nbe prepared to deal with whatever might\nemerge from the depths. Most impressive.
Uh...yeeees. That's exactly what I'm doing.
You are a Paladyn true. It's no wonder you\npassed the entrance exam so easily.
It is most reassuring to have you fighting\nat my side.
Y-you will be counting on ME?!\nEr, I mean... Yes, of course, Elisanne!\nI am happy to help how I can!
Now let us keep our eyes peeled and\ncontinue on—for this jungle is nothing\nin the face of OUR mighty duo!
...Hmm. We'll have to hack through that\ncreeper vine to proceed any further.
No, thanks to your quick thinking.\nWhat IS this thing, exactly...?
I believe someone used that vine\nas the trigger for a trap.
But who would put such a thing in the\nmiddle of the jungle—and why?
Perhaps there really IS something here.\n...Treasure, I mean.
That would go some way toward\nexplaining the presence of a trap.
In that case, we must be ever more\ncautious as we press forward.
So long as we keep a watch for any\nrogue vines, I think we should...
Ugh. How shameful of me to fall\nfor such an obvious ploy.
How dare you string up Elly!\nWhat an insolent trap!\nHold on, I'll cut you down...
By the way...did you refer to me\nas ＂Elly＂ just a moment ago?
WHAAAT?! Uh, I mean...of course not?
Hmm. Well, I WAS hanging in mid-air,\nso perhaps it interfered with my hearing.
...Which means that singing must also\nbe my ears playing tricks—although it\nis a rather beautiful trick, if so!
I'm certain you are imagining...\nWait! I hear it too!
It is so beautiful... I feel I could\nlose myself in it forever...
It's the most...lovely song I've ever heard...
I must find the owner of that voice!
It is coming from this directi...
Oh no! Something has my ankle!
Fie, now we are BOTH caught in this trap!
We are both well, Highness, thank you.\nBut whatever are you doing here?
I came to see how you two were faring.\nGlad to see you're all right, more or less.
Would you care to explain why we found\nthe two of you dangling in mid-air?
This jungle is laden with traps.
Traps? Who would do such a thing?!
Someone who wanted to keep\na treasure safe, perhaps?
We were attempting to answer that very\nquestion, but then the singing began\nand... Well, you see the result.
I fear that song captivated us utterly.
Hmm. That sounds like Siren's doing.
Siren is a legendary dragon whose\ngorgeous voice has the power to\nmesmerize people.
I knew that was no mere song!
So long as we keep our ears covered,\nwe should be all right going forward.
Inconvenient, but certainly not\nthe end of the world.
How do you know so much\nabout this dragon, Estelle?
I heard the tales in my early Church days.\nIn truth, she struck me as a rather\nbothersome sort of dragon.
Sometimes I forget that you used to be\na preacher in the Ilian Church.
And exactly how does one ＂forget＂\nsuch a key fact of someone's life?!
Well, I'm preeetty sure preachers don't\nnormally run around in swimsuits.
M-my clothing is not the issue here!\nRegardless of dress, I assure you that\nmy heart remains that of a preacher!
N-now then, let us be off to\ncheck on Ranzal and Celliera.
Good idea. We should warn them about\nthe traps—and Siren as well.
Let's track them down before\ntrouble does it first!
